{"type":"message","id":"441d6ccf","parentId":"941ebdad","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:37:41.056Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_e3dsncm3bcaf_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 103522\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/cfi_compression_experiment.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent status:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI Analysis done - found that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe most logical next step is to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would:\r\n1. Compare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline\r\n2. Test whether prioritizing high-CFI tokens improves next-pulse prediction\r\n3. Advance the \"Pending\" item directly\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist related to this experiment. The CFI analysis is in `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`. I need to design and potentially implement the experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, the most concrete action would be to create the experiment design/plan and potentially start the implementation. But given Breakaway is stateless and the pulse script handles execution, I should probably write a script or document that advances this.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what specific file edit would best advance the CFI-weighted compression experiment:\r\n\r\n1. I could create a new script `scripts/cfi_compression_experiment.ps1` that implements the comparison\r\n2. I could update `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` with the experiment plan\r\n3. I could create a test harness\r\n\r\nGiven the focus on file edits and concrete action, creating an experiment script seems most direct. But I need to be careful - this is a new file creation.\r\n\r\nLet me draft the experiment script that would:\r\n1. Load the frequency invariants data\r\n2. Apply CFI weighting\r\n3. Compare prediction accuracy vs frequency baseline\r\n4. Output results\r\n\r\nThis advances the \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\" pending task.\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n- Reads the CFI analysis data\r\n\r\n\r\n- Implements both weighting approaches for direct comparison\r\n- Provides a clear metric for evaluating performance differences\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that only 5.7% of frequency-invariants are true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7). The pending experiment comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency-baseline compression has a clear path: apply the CFI scores as weights, compress differently, and measure prediction quality.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the CFI-weighted compression experiment script that implements the comparison test, enabling direct measurement of whether prioritizing high-CFI tokens improves next-pulse prediction over frequency-only approaches.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests whether CFI-scored token prioritization improves next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline\r\n# Phase: Phase 1 Advancement - pending task\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Configuration\r\n$CFI_RESULTS = \"research/CFI_RESULTS.md\"\r\n$PULSE_DIR = \"pulses\"\r\n$OUTPUT = \"research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n\r\n# Phase 1: Parse CFI scores from analysis\r\nWrite-Host \"`n[1/4] Parsing CFI scores...\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n$cfiData = @{}\r\n$inVariantTable = $false\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem $PULSE_DIR -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name -Descending | Select-Object -First 20\r\n\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pulse.FullName -Raw\r\n    # Extract frequency-invariant tokens (lines starting with - `)\r\n    if ($content -match 'Frequency Invariants.*?---') {\r\n        $matches = [regex]::Matches($content, '^\\- `([^`]+)`.*?CFI=([0-9.]+)', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Multiline)\r\n        foreach ($match in $matches) {\r\n            $token = $match.Groups[1].Value.Trim()\r\n            $cfi = [double]$match.Groups[2].Value\r\n            $cfiData[$token] = $cfi\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$totalTokens = $cfiData.Count\r\n$highCFI = ($cfiData.Values | Where-Object { $_ -ge 0.7 }).Count\r\n$zeroCFI = ($cfiData.Values | Where-Object { $_ -eq 0 }).Count\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"  Parsed $totalTokens unique tokens\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\nWrite-Host \"  High CFI (>=0.7): $highCFI ($([math]::Round($highCFI/$totalTokens*100,1))%)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"  Zero CFI: $zeroCFI ($([math]::Round($zeroCFI/$totalTokens*100,1))%)\"\r\n\r\n# Phase 2: Simulate compression with both methods\r\nWrite-Host \"`n[2/4] Simulating compression methods...\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n\r\n$compressionBudget = 50  # tokens to keep per pulse\r\n\r\n# Method A: Frequency-only (baseline)\r\n# Method B: CFI-weighted (experimental)\r\n\r\n# Build frequency table from all pulses\r\n$freqTable = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pulse.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '`([^`]+)`') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value }\r\n    foreach ($token in $tokens) {\r\n        $freqTable[$token] = ($freqTable[$token] ?? 0) + 1\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Select top-k by frequency (baseline)\r\n$freqTopK = ($freqTable\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:35:58\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774363061051}}
